When I try to run the command I get an error, which I don't understand, since I ran this commands.

```
nvim git:feature/dev-153-setup-black-atom-core
‚ùØ black-atom-core generate
error: Relative import path "@std/yaml" not prefixed with / or ./ or ../
  hint: If you want to use a JSR or npm package, try running `deno add jsr:@std/yaml` or `deno add npm:@std/yaml`
    at file:///Users/nbr/repos/black-atom-industries/core/src/cli.ts:2:35
```
The error is occurring because of how the import is written in `cli.ts`. Even though you've specified the import map in `deno.json`, you need to reference the import alias correctly in your code.

Change this line in `core/src/cli.ts`:

```ts
import { parse as parseYml } from "@std/yaml";
```

to:

```ts
import { parse as parseYml } from "@std/yaml/parse.ts";
```

The main issue is that you need to specify the exact module file you want to import from the package. The JSR standard library modules typically expose their functionality through specific files.

After making this change, the import should work correctly with your import map configuration.

Also, make sure you've installed the dependencies by running:

```bash
deno cache --reload src/cli.ts
```

This will ensure all dependencies are properly cached and available.
